You can set these facts in a class (look at params.pp for example) or as facts
on a system, facter_dot_d.rb from stdlib by default looks in 
/etc/facter/facts.d/facts.yaml.

By populating that file with facts, you can dynamically change your vsftpd.conf
and puppet will automatically restart vsftpd. This also lends itself to be
updated via mcollective and it's mc-etc-facts plugin.

There are also the following facts that are used to populate other vsftpd
config files.

vsftpd_chroot_users    - A comma or space separated list of users to populate
                         /etc/vsftpd.d/vsftpd.chroot_users

vsftpd_banned_emails   - A comma or space separated list of email addresses 
                         to populate /etc/vsftpd.d/vsftpd.banned_emails

vsftpd_email_passwords - A comma or space separated list of passwords to 
                         populate /etc/vsftpd.d/vsftpd.chroot_users

vsftpd_users_list      - A comma or space separated list of users to populate
                         /etc/vsftpd.d/vsftpd.userlist_file

== CAVEATS:

May work on other platforms. Only tested on Ubuntu 12.04. Currently
Ubuntu/Debian is only explicitly supported vi the params.pp. You can add other
OS support via that class.

